s that monitoring data appears in the monitoring cluster. The Metricbeat `.monitoring-es-*` indices are what really matter here.\n\nI need to think through the `scope` setting for Metricbeat's Elasticsearch module. Using `scope: node` makes sense for a sidecar since each pod gets its own instance, but that means cluster-level metrics like health status might be incomplete. With `scope: cluster`, I'd get comprehensive metrics but risk duplication across multiple sidecars — so `scope: node` is the better choice despite the tradeoff.\n\nNow I'm ready to implement this. I'll create ConfigMaps for both Metricbeat and Filebeat configurations, then patch the StatefulSets to add the sidecar containers and mount the configs. The tricky part will be using strategic merge patches to add volumeMounts to existing containers while introducing new ones.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":309,"cache_read_input_tokens":46332,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":309},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"522e4a02-084e-40aa-a726-be4cb5527c3b","uuid":"0014d82a-3faf-4fa2-916b-1c2276da5c9e","request_id":"req_011CcM7g2Czsr3CJHU6o7QAN"}
