{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Wk856soePLiyHRPSmUUhVR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both monitoring indices are now appearing in the monitoring cluster:\n1. `.monitoring-es-8-mb` - 41 documents from Metricbeat (ES metrics)\n2. `.ds-.monitoring-beats-8-2026.06.24-2026.06.24-000001` - 4383 documents from Filebeat (logs)\n\nThe monitoring data flow is now working! The JSON decode errors in Filebeat are just because ES is writing GC logs in non-JSON format (the `gc.log`, `gc.log.00`, `gc.log.01` files). These aren't real ES structured logs. ES 8.x by default writes its main logs to STDOUT and to `*.json` files, but since we mounted the `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs` volume, the main ES JSON logs may not be there yet (they would only appear when there's something to log).\nThe GC logs are causing JSON parsing failures in Filebeat, but the events are still being shipped with error flags, and we already have 4383 documents in the monitoring index. I should update the Filebeat config to skip JSON parsing on the `*.log` files and only parse the `*_server.json` files to clean this up, though it's mostly cosmetic at this point. Let me also double-check the Metricbeat data more carefully—with 5 pods each sending metrics every 10 seconds, I want to verify the ES cluster is receiving everything properly. The GC logs in the volume aren't structured JSON data, and ES is writing its actual logs to stdout in container mode anyway, so Filebeat doesn't have much useful structured data to parse. The monitoring is working fine through Metricbeat, and even though Filebeat is shipping GC logs with parse errors, it's still creating the monitoring indices. I should simplify the Filebeat config to remove the unnecessary JSON parsing logic.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":971,"cache_read_input_tokens":62986,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":971},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"522e4a02-084e-40aa-a726-be4cb5527c3b","uuid":"9964ff18-5063-4622-98f4-c1b16ec662d2","request_id":"req_011CcM8C5aVCvPkzUmDfuLdK"}
