{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016fuBczqbrzzLEvqSvRPy5j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `.geoip_databases` index has both primary and replica shards unassigned. The primary shard is unassigned due to `NODE_LEFT` and the replica is `PRIMARY_FAILED`. This is a serious issue - the primary shard lost its allocation when a node left (during the rolling restart), and then the primary failed.\n\nThis is the `.geoip_databases` index - it's an internal Elasticsearch index used for GeoIP enrichment. Let me check if we can fix this.\n\nThe issue is:\n1. Primary shard 0 of `.geoip_databases` is unassigned due to `NODE_LEFT`\n2. The replica can't be assigned without a primary shard first\n\nI can fix this using the cluster reroute API to allocate an empty primary, which will clear the existing data but restore functionality. The GeoIP data isn't critical since it can be rebuilt. Let me try forcing a retry of the allocation first before resorting to that.\n\nActually, I should check the allocation explain to understand what's really happening with the `.geoip_databases` index — this unassigned state might have existed before my changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":495,"cache_read_input_tokens":67222,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":495},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"522e4a02-084e-40aa-a726-be4cb5527c3b","uuid":"437001b9-c862-45a9-a664-8017c56360e3","request_id":"req_011CcM8GKbxWDwvVbXha759K"}
