{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012hNTDgsm3MLFkqAWowMkhW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working correctly. Here's a summary of what was done and the final state:\n\n---\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Created two ConfigMaps** (`metricbeat-config` and `filebeat-config`) in the `elasticsearch` namespace with configurations to ship data to `monitoring-es-http.monitoring.svc.cluster.local:9200`.\n\n2. **Patched both StatefulSets** (`es-cluster` and `es-data`) via strategic merge patch to add:\n   - A shared `es-logs` emptyDir volume (mounted at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs` in both the ES container and the Filebeat sidecar)\n   - A **Metricbeat 8.11.1** sidecar connecting to `https://localhost:9200` with the TLS CA cert and elastic credentials\n   - A **Filebeat 8.11.1** sidecar reading ES log files and shipping to the monitoring cluster\n\n3. **Recovered `.geoip_databases`** shard after the rolling restart left it with no valid copy (force-allocated empty primary; ES repopulated it automatically).\n\n**Final state:**\n\n| Check | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| Source ES cluster health | **green**, 5 nodes |\n| All 5 ES pods | **3/3 Running** (elasticsearch + metricbeat + filebeat) |\n| `.monitoring-es-8-mb` index | **1,385+ docs** (growing, Metricbeat xpack format) |\n| `.ds-metricbeat-8.11.1-*` data stream | **337+ docs** (Metricbeat data stream) |\n| `.ds-.monitoring-beats-8-*` data stream | **10,481+ docs** (Filebeat logs) |\n| Metricbeat node_stats | **3 successes / 10s** per node |"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":194,"cache_read_input_tokens":86883,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":194},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"